==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|consensus|lang=la||agreement, accordance, unanimity}} < {{term|consentire||to agree}}; see {{term|consent}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# [[general#Adjective|General]] agreement among the members of a given group or community, each of which exercises some discretion in decision-making and follow-up action.
# Average projected value, as in the finance term consensus forecast.
# A standard of [[w:Decision making#Decision making in social setting|decision-making]] where agreement is defined as the lack of active opposition to the proposed course of action.

